{"lemma":"بَكْرَةٍ","slug":"بَكْرَةٍ","root":"ب.ك.ر","root_slug":"ب-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ك-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَكْرَةٍ","root":"بكر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3073","n3074","n3075"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"early morning"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"early in the morning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pulley, block, wheel in a simple machine"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare بَكَرَ (bakara, “to be early”). Unrelated to Hebrew בקר (bóqer, “morning”) despite similarity in form and meaning.\n\nAdverbial accusative of بُكْرَة (bukra, “early morning”).\n\nFrom the ideas of rising early of بَكَرَ (bakara) or بَكَّرَ (bakkara), i.e. anticipating the movement of the axle or rope and being placed into position before."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3073","headword_ar":"بَكْرَةٌ","root":"bkr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarapN","text_ar":"بَكَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing upon which [passes the rope wherewith] one draws water"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a well [or the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) [ i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheave of a pulley;] a round piece of wood, in the middle [of the circumference] whereof is a groove"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the rope, and in the interior"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"centre] whereof is an axis upon which it turns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quick"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAlap","text_ar":"مَحَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large sheave of a pulley"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) [but MF disapproves of this last explanation: sometimes, by a synecdoche, it is used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pulley"},{"kind":"text","text":"complete:] the pl. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarN","text_ar":"بَكَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) a pl. of the former, anomalous, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaqN","text_ar":"حَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaloqapN","text_ar":"حَلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaA^N","text_ar":"حَمَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoA^apN","text_ar":"حَمْاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or of the latter; (Msb;) or a coll. gen. n., of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarapN","text_ar":"بَكَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.; (MF;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakaraAt","text_ar":"بَكَرَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) a pl. of the former [as well as of the latter]. (S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  Hence, app., the former signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small ring, like a bead, in the ornamental part of a sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [and the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakaraAtN","text_ar":"بَكَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rings that are attached to the ornamental part"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the scabbard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rings called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatax","text_ar":"قَتَخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are worn upon the fingers or toes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of women."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, perhaps,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An assembly, a company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a congregated body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA EalaY bakorapi A^abiyhimo","text_ar":"جَاوُوا عَلَى بَكْرَةِ اَبِيهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov., (TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came together, not one remaining behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came all of them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, IJ, A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without exception:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came in a multitude, and all together, none remaining behind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came in succession, one after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the heels of, another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came in one way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As:) [accord. to some, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bkrp","text_ar":"بكرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explained in the next preceding sentence; and, if so,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa","text_ar":"مَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$otamiliyna","text_ar":"مُشْتَمِلِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is understood before it: or it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bkrp","text_ar":"بكرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ a youthful she-camel; ” and thus implies that they were few: (see Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 312:) or] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bak~arotu fiY ka*aA","text_ar":"بَكَّرْتُ فِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ I was, ” or “ became, ” or “ went, ” “ before in such a thing; ” so that it signifies that they came from first to last: (IJ:) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bkrp","text_ar":"بكرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses explained in this paragraph; though in this case there is no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bkrp","text_ar":"بكرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in reality. (AO, S. *)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","M","Mgh","AA","IJ","A","AO","As"]},{"entry_id":"n3074","headword_ar":"بُكْرَةٌ","root":"bkr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarN","text_ar":"بَكَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"early morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part of the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xix. 12 and xxxiii. 41 and xlviii. 9, as relating to the former word; and K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the time of the prayer of daybreak and sunrise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibokaArN","text_ar":"اـِبْكَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. in the same sense, (K,) accord. to the lexicologists, as Sb says; but he adds that he holds it to be [only] the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abokara","text_ar":"اَبْكَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA: [and the like is said in the S with reference to its occurrence in the Kur iii. 36 and xl."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"57:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) pl. [of pauc.] of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abokaArN","text_ar":"اَبْكَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukarN","text_ar":"بُكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu bukorapN","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ بُكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarFA","text_ar":"بَكَرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAkirKA","text_ar":"بَاكِرٍا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him early in the morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, A, Msb.) But if you mean the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukorapN","text_ar":"بُكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a particular day, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu bukorapa","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ بُكْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making the noun imperfectly decl.; [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him early in the morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and in this case it is not to be used otherwise than as an adv. n. of time. (S.) If you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAkirFA","text_ar":"بَاكِرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", using this word as an epithet, you use"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAkirap","text_ar":"بَاكِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the fem. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro EalaY farasika bukorapF","text_ar":"سِرْ عَلَى فَرَسِكَ بُكْرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakarFA","text_ar":"بَكَرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou on thy horse early in the morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarFA","text_ar":"سَحَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA. [But in two copies of the S, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sro","text_ar":"سرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra","text_ar":"سِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n3075","headword_ar":"بَكَرَةٌ","root":"bkr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakorapN","text_ar":"بَكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}